<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="422" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1380,2019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1380,1405]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Upper division of eye about 
<number box="[610,620,1380,1404]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[630,660,1380,1404]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="10.0">10</number>
as large as lower division. Rs straight, as long as r-m. Each lobe of cercus pentagonal, posterior margin tapered medially; outer gonostylus swollen and slightly notched apically in lateral view; inner gonocoxal lobe transparent, slender, swollen apically, bar-like.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="423" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1380,2019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,422,1487,1512]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Body length 4.0 mm, wing length 
<quantity box="[830,921,1487,1512]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
, wing width 2.0 mm. Head uniformly black. Ocellar triangle black. Head mostly without hairs, except eyes with a row of several long hairs along dorsal margin. Compound eyes dichoptic, boundary of upper division and lower division unconspicuous; upper division smaller than lower division, about 
<number box="[456,466,1596,1620]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[476,506,1596,1620]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="10.0">10</number>
as large as lower division, brick-red with pubescences; lower division black with pubescences; ocelli brick-red, prominent. Antenna longer than head width, scape and pedicel short, first flagellomere constricted basally, other flagellomeres elliptic; antenna uniformly dark brown with brown short hairs. Proboscis dark brown with brown hairs. Palpus five-segmented, first segment short, brown; segments 
<number box="[1394,1436,1704,1728]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2–3</number>
long, yellow with brown hairs; segments 
<number box="[614,655,1740,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
dark brown with brown hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1380,2019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Thoracic tergum uniformly dark brown. Thoracic pleuron mostly dark brown except metapleuron brown. Only scutellum with dense patches of hairs on anterior margin. Legs mostly brown except coxae, trochanters and bases of femora yellow brown; trochanters with black spots anteriorly; legs with uniformly short black hairs, fore trochanter with two black long hairs. Tibiae without spurs. Wing (
<figureCitation box="[919,989,1884,1909]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1828,1851]" captionTargetBox="[372,1211,598,1802]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[366,1220,591,1807]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 2. Blepharicera asiatica (Brodsky) (male). 1. Habitus of male, lateral view; 2: Wing. Scale bar: 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226445/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Fig. 
<number box="[974,989,1884,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
) subhyaline, apically with light brown cloud; veins brown. Sc rudimentary, not ending at base of Rs; apex of R 
<number box="[962,970,1934,1948]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="1.0">1</number>
slightly rudimentary; Rs straight, as long as r-m; r-m straight. Base of halter yellow, with light hairs; apex of halter dark brown, with short black hairs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1380,2019]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,536]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="423" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Abdominal tergites mainly dark brown except tergites 
<number box="[808,850,1994,2019]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" value="4.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="2.0">2–6</number>
with brown band anteriorly, sternites mostly brown, each sternite with light brown band anteriorly; abdomen with short black hairs. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1307,1422,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1460,1483]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,201,1428]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[150,1436,193,1439]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 5. Blepharicera asiatica (Brodsky) (male). 3: Genitalia, dorsal view; 4: Genitalia, ventral view; 5: Gonostylus, dorsal view. Scale bar: 4 – 5 = 0.5 mm. Abbreviations: c = cercus; ep = epandrium; gs = gonostylus; gx = gonocoxite; hyd = hypandrium; og = outer gonostylus; ig = inner gonostylus; pa = parameres." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/226446/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
Figs. 
<number box="[1377,1422,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5</number>
</figureCitation>
): Posterior margin epandrium of concaved medially, with uniformly short hairs; hypandrium rectangular, slightly narrow basally, posteromedial margin concave; cercus bilobate, each lobe of cercus pentagonal, posterior margin tapered medially, with uniformly short hairs; outer gonostylus swollen and slightly notched apically in lateral view, with uniformly hairs; inner gonocoxal lobe transparent, slender, swollen apically, bar-like; paramere slender, transparent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,536]" box="[199,418,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="423">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
